The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for graphs, which is a topic in theoretical computer science related to data structures and algorithms. Specifically, the paper presents a new algorithm for assigning labels to nodes in a graph such that the distance between any two nodes can be determined from their labels. This topic is closely related to data structures and graph algorithms, which are covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category, as it covers topics related to efficient data structures for storing and manipulating data. "cs.CG" (Computational Geometry) is also likely, as it covers topics related to algorithms for geometric problems, which can be applied to graph problems. "cs.DM" (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category, as it covers topics related to combinatorics and graph theory. "cs.IT" (Information Theory) is also possible, as it covers topics related to coding theory, which can be applied to designing efficient labeling schemes. Finally, "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible, as it covers topics related to network analysis, which can be applied to graph problems.
